{"TopicId":145790,"ForumId":16,"TopicTitle":"Drills, how to properly mount them","CreatedByName":"Loren Pechtel","CreatedById":157006,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-08-11T19:09:54Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Loren Pechtel","CreatedById":157006,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-08-11T19:09:54Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI finally got the initial pieces of my mining base to Minmus.\u00A0 Engineer\u0027s hut (serves as the hub), a drill/ore tank/ISRU/cooling assembly and a fuel/solar cell/fuel cell assembly.\u00A0 (Monoprop and Xenon storage to follow.)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nLink them up, deploy the drills--what\u0027s this, the drill just lifted the whole tower it\u0027s part of into the sky?\u00A0 It also lifted the hub into the sky, although the fuel tank was heavy enough it stayed put.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThat just sounds like it\u0027s asking for the Kracken to pay a visit.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Kyrt Malthorn","CreatedById":149101,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-08-11T21:21:14Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMaybe this will help?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022NyNTAni.jpg\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022625\u0022 src=\u0022http://i.imgur.com/NyNTAni.jpg\u0022 width=\u00221000\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe upper section\u00A0of the extended drill\u0027s telescopic (extending)\u00A0pole\u00A0is considered a \u0022solid\u0022 object. \u00A0The lower\u00A0half (and the drill head) are visual only and can clip into the dirt. \u00A0The seperation between these sections is a visible downsize in the pole\u0027s diameter.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYou can right click on drills in the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Vehicle Assembly Building\u0022\u003EVAB\u003C/abbr\u003E and view them extended, and plan their placement based on your landing gear height.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-08-11T21:22:39Z\u0022 title=\u002208/11/2016 09:22  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00227 yr\u0022\u003EAugust 11, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by Kyrt Malthorn\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Loren Pechtel","CreatedById":157006,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-08-11T22:54:53Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222713756\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022145790\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221470950474\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022149101\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Kyrt Malthorn\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, Kyrt Malthorn said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMaybe this will help?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022http://i.imgur.com/NyNTAni.jpg\u0022 title=\u0022Enlarge image\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022NyNTAni.jpg\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage ipsImage_thumbnailed\u0022 height=\u0022625\u0022 src=\u0022http://i.imgur.com/NyNTAni.jpg\u0022 width=\u00221000\u0022\u003E\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe upper section\u00A0of the extended drill\u0027s telescopic (extending)\u00A0pole\u00A0is considered a \u0022solid\u0022 object. \u00A0The lower\u00A0half (and the drill head) are visual only and can clip into the dirt. \u00A0The seperation between these sections is a visible downsize in the pole\u0027s diameter.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYou can right click on drills in the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Vehicle Assembly Building\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Vehicle Assembly Building\u0022\u003EVAB\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E and view them extended, and plan their placement based on your landing gear height.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThank you very much!\u00A0 That\u0027s a crazy design, it should be acceptable to mount them flush with the bottom of the craft.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Kyrt Malthorn","CreatedById":149101,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-08-12T02:28:21Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222713882\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022145790\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221470956093\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022157006\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Loren Pechtel\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n3 hours ago, Loren Pechtel said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThank you very much!\u00A0 That\u0027s a crazy design, it should be acceptable to mount them flush with the bottom of the craft.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nFound the pic with Google, looks like someone else was trying to figure out where the \u0027bottom\u0027 of the drill was, too. \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:P\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_tongue.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:P\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"StrandedonEarth","CreatedById":89439,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-08-12T02:41:07Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIf you have \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Kerbal Inventory System (mod)\u0022\u003EKIS\u003C/abbr\u003E/\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Kerbal Attachment System (mod)\u0022\u003EKAS\u003C/abbr\u003E, you can get your engineer to remount them. I had to do that myself once when I mounted the drills too low.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Loren Pechtel","CreatedById":157006,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-08-12T02:45:09Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222714078\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022145790\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221470968901\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022149101\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Kyrt Malthorn\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n15 minutes ago, Kyrt Malthorn said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nFound the pic with Google, looks like someone else was trying to figure out where the \u0027bottom\u0027 of the drill was, too. \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:P\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_tongue.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:P\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThere were enough things messed up I finally reverted to the save I made before embarking on building a mining base.\u00A0 I stupidly put my EVA resource pipes in inventory, not realizing they had to be on the rocket.\u00A0 You can\u0027t mount the first end of them.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Blaarkies","CreatedById":153700,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-08-12T05:44:24Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222713617\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022145790\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221470942594\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022157006\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Loren Pechtel\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n10 hours ago, Loren Pechtel said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI finally got the initial pieces of my mining base to Minmus.\u00A0 Engineer\u0027s hut (serves as the hub), a drill/ore tank/ISRU/cooling assembly and a fuel/solar cell/fuel cell assembly.\u00A0 (Monoprop and Xenon storage to follow.)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nLink them up, deploy the drills--what\u0027s this, the drill just lifted the whole tower it\u0027s part of into the sky?\u00A0 It also lifted the hub into the sky, although the fuel tank was heavy enough it stayed put.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThat just sounds like it\u0027s asking for the Kracken to pay a visit.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nFALSE!\u00A0Minmus has no \u0022sky\u0022 !\u003Cbr\u003E\njust kidding\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:rolleyes:\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_rolleyes.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:rolleyes:\u0022\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\nAbout the Xenon storage...are you playing with some mods? In Stock/vanilla KSP there is no mining/converting to Xenon...the only place to get Xenon gas is at the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Vehicle Assembly Building\u0022\u003EVAB\u003C/abbr\u003E or \u003Cabbr title=\u0022SpacePlane Hangar\u0022\u003ESPH\u003C/abbr\u003E, nowhere else\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\n...but, you could get edit your ISRU\u0027s \u0022part.cfg\u0022 file. Just\u00A0add the ability to convert ore to xenon\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:sealed:\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_lipssealed.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:sealed:\u0022\u003E\u00A0(\u0022ModuleManager\u0022 mod is great for this)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Loren Pechtel","CreatedById":157006,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-08-12T14:33:12Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222714194\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022145790\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221470980664\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022153700\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Blaarkies\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n8 hours ago, Blaarkies said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nFALSE!\u00A0Minmus has no \u0022sky\u0022 !\u003Cbr\u003E\njust kidding\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:rolleyes:\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_rolleyes.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:rolleyes:\u0022\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\nAbout the Xenon storage...are you playing with some mods? In Stock/vanilla KSP there is no mining/converting to Xenon...the only place to get Xenon gas is at the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Vehicle Assembly Building\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Vehicle Assembly Building\u0022\u003EVAB\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E or \u003Cabbr title=\u0022SpacePlane Hangar\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022SpacePlane Hangar\u0022\u003ESPH\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E, nowhere else\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\n...but, you could get edit your ISRU\u0027s \u0022part.cfg\u0022 file. Just\u00A0add the ability to convert ore to xenon\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:sealed:\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_lipssealed.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:sealed:\u0022\u003E\u00A0(\u0022ModuleManager\u0022 mod is great for this)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThere isn\u0027t?\u00A0 Ok, no need for xenon storage.\u00A0 I haven\u0027t ever played with the ion drive, I hadn\u0027t noticed it couldn\u0027t be refined.\u00A0 I\u0027m not sure I even care, I\u0027m looking at putting mining bases on the smallest body of every system, I can afford to burn harder.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Blaarkies","CreatedById":153700,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-08-15T06:04:12Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222714477\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022145790\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221471012392\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022157006\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Loren Pechtel\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 8/12/2016 at 4:33 PM, Loren Pechtel said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThere isn\u0027t?\u00A0 Ok, no need for xenon storage.\u00A0 I haven\u0027t ever played with the ion drive, I hadn\u0027t noticed it couldn\u0027t be refined.\u00A0 I\u0027m not sure I even care, I\u0027m looking at putting mining bases on the smallest body of every system, I can afford to burn harder.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIon drives really only suits a small portion of the player base...try sending a tiny ion powered probe to some interplanetary destination. If that didn\u0027t frustrate you, then you might start building ion tug-\u003Cs\u003Eboat\u003C/s\u003Eships\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:D\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_cheesy.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:D\u0022\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\nOnce you have a refinery on Minmus, nuclear tugs become really, really cheap(maybe almost free?). As long as you go \u003Cstrong\u003Ebig\u003C/strong\u003E, there is no way that Xenon power can compete.\u003Cbr\u003E\n*\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv style=\u0022margin-bottom:0px;font-weight:lighter;font-size:xx-large;font-family:arial, \u0027sans-serif-light\u0027, sans-serif;color:rgb(34,34,34);font-style:normal;letter-spacing:normal;line-height:normal;text-align:left;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;word-spacing:0px;background-color:rgb(255,255,255);\u0022\u003E\nbig\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv style=\u0022color:rgb(34,34,34);font-family:arial, sans-serif;font-size:small;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;letter-spacing:normal;line-height:normal;text-align:left;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;word-spacing:0px;background-color:rgb(255,255,255);\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv style=\u0022font-size:large;\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cspan\u003Eba-eeg-!\u003C/span\u003E/\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv\u003E\n\u003Cdiv style=\u0022padding-top:10px;\u0022\u003E\n\u003Ci\u003E\u003Cspan\u003Enoun(as used here)\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/i\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv style=\u0022color:rgb(135,135,135);\u0022\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Col style=\u0022margin:0px;padding:0px 0px 0px 20px;border:0px;\u0022\u003E\u003Cli style=\u0022margin:0px;padding:0px;border:0px;list-style:none;\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv style=\u0022font-weight:lighter;font-size:small;font-family:arial, \u0027sans-serif-light\u0027, sans-serif;padding-top:10px;\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv style=\u0022float:left;\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003E1\u003C/strong\u003E.\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv style=\u0022margin-left:20px;\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv style=\u0022font-size:small;\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003Emultiple\u00A0\u003Ca href=\u0022http://wiki.kerbalspaceprogram.com/wiki/Mk3_Liquid_Fuel_Fuselage_Long\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003EMk3_Liquid_Fuel_Fuselage_Long\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0tanks filled with many, many liquid fuels filled up to the brim, loaded on top of some lander contraption hoisted by multiple\u00A0\u003Ca hre